              <Attribute Type="Description">In a family with typical features of familial platelet disorder with predisposition to acute myelogenous leukemia (FPDMM; 601399), Michaud et al. (2002) found a 1-bp deletion in the splice donor site of intron 4 of the RUNX1 gene (IVS4+3delA). The novel transcript resulting from use of a cryptic donor site resulted in frameshift after amino acid 135, addition of 41 unrelated residues, and termination at codon 177 (Arg135fsTer177).</Attribute>
